---
eleventyImport:
    collections: ["post"]
layout: base.njk
title: Freelance UX designer and service designer, UK – Dan Sensecall
description: Freelance UX designer and service designer helping UK organisations design user-centred digital services. Specialising in government and public sector projects.
permalink: /
---

<section id="introduction"
         aria-labelledby="introduction-title"
         class="py-8 lg:py-12">
    <div class="max-w-4xl">
        <p class="heading-l flex items-center mb-[clamp(1rem,0.9rem+0.5vw,1.375rem)] max-[480px]:text-[clamp(1.35rem,1.1rem+1.8vw,1.64rem)]">
            <img src="/assets/images/dan-sensecall.jpg"
                 alt="Dan Sensecall"
                 class="rounded-full mr-2 lg:mr-3 max-[480px]:mr-1 shadow-sm w-10 h-10 md:w-12 md:h-12"
                 width="64"
                 height="64">
            <span class="ml-2 max-[480px]:ml-1">Hi! I'm Dan Sensecall.</span>
        </p>
        <h1 id="introduction-title"
            class="body-m lg:w-4/5 mb-5 font-[var(--font-family-base)] font-normal">
            Freelance UX designer &amp; service design consultant from the UK.
        </h1>
        <p class="body-m">
            I help public sector, charity and government teams untangle messy problems, improve live services, and design long-term, user-centred solutions that meet the needs of citizens, civil servants and public sector workers.
        </p>
    </div>
</section>
<section id="clients">
    <div class="flex flex-col gap-6 md:gap-12">
        <div class="lg:w-2/3 order-2 md:order-2">
            <h2 class="heading-m sr-only md:not-sr-only">
                Organisations who I've helped
            </h2>
            <p class="body-m">
                Over the past 15 years, I've worked with startups, government
                departments and FTSE 100 companies to improve their products and services. Since 2018, I've worked exclusively with Public Sector organisations to design services for
                citizens and internal users.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="lg:w-2/3 order-1 md:order-3 grid grid-cols-3 sm:grid-cols-3 md:grid-cols-4 gap-x-2 gap-y-5 sm:gap-x-4 sm:gap-y-6 md:gap-y-8 py-4 md:py-0">
            {% for logo in collections.logos %}
                <div class="flex items-center justify-start"
                     role="img"
                     aria-label="{{ logo.name }}">
                    <img src="/assets/images/clients/{{ logo.image | replace('.svg', '--dark.svg') if (logo.image.endsWith('.svg')) else logo.image }}"
                         alt="{{ logo.name }} logo"
                         width="100"
                         height="50"
                         class="hidden dark:block w-full max-w-[90px] sm:max-w-[100px] md:max-w-[120px] lg:max-w-[120px] xl:max-w-[140px] 2xl:max-w-[160px] h-auto object-contain" />
                    <img src="/assets/images/clients/{{ logo.image }}"
                         alt="{{ logo.name }} logo"
                         width="100"
                         height="50"
                         class="dark:hidden w-full max-w-[90px] sm:max-w-[100px] md:max-w-[120px] lg:max-w-[120px] xl:max-w-[140px] 2xl:max-w-[160px] h-auto object-contain" />
                </div>
            {% endfor %}
        </div>
        <div class="lg:w-2/3 order-3 md:order-1">
            <p class="body-m">You should work with me if you need help with:</p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-5 body-m">
                <li><strong>service design</strong> for complex, end-to-end services</li>
                <li><strong>interaction design</strong> for intuitive user journeys and interfaces</li>
                <li><strong>user research</strong> to understand user needs, behaviours and pain points</li>
                <li><strong>accessibility</strong> to create more inclusive and usable digital services</li>
                <li><strong>content design</strong> to make information clearer, simpler and easier to use</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
<section id="services" aria-labelledby="services-title" class="py-8 md:py-10 lg:py-12 xl:py-14 mt-10">
    <div class="lg:w-2/3">
        <h2 id="services-title"
            class="heading-m">
            What I do
        </h2>
        <p class="body-m">
            I help teams make their services more user-friendly, effective and accessible. I focus on putting humans first, understanding their needs and working with organisations to create services that really work for people who use them.
        </p>
        <p class="body-m">
            As well as making things simpler for users, I make sure to deliver measurable results and value for the organisations I work with.
        </p>
    </div>
    {% set services = [
            {
                "title": "Service design",
                "description": "This means looking at users' end-to-end journeys, and thinking about how the different services, or parts of a service, work together.",
            "link": {
                "url": "https://www.gov.uk/guidance/service-designer",
                "text": "Read more about service design"
            },
            "image": "/assets/images/illustration-sketches/service-blueprint.webp",
            "imageAlt": "A diagram showing a service design blueprint with connected flow steps",
            "colour": "text-emerald-600 dark:text-emerald-400"
            },
            {
                "title": "Interaction design",
                "description": "This involves designing the things that people interact with, and the way it responds. It's more detailed than service design, and often focuses on the user interface (UI) and the content (words and images).",
                "link": {
                    "url": "https://www.usability.gov/what-and-why/interaction-design.html",
                    "text": "Read more about interaction design"
                },
                "image": "/assets/images/illustration-sketches/interaction-design.webp",
                "imageAlt": "A diagram showing a user interaction flow with connected steps",
                "icon": "sparkles",
                "colour": "text-stone-600 dark:text-stone-400"
            },
            {
                "title": "User research",
                "description": "This means talking to people who use the service, and finding out what they need. It also means testing the service with people to see if it works for them.",
                "link": {
                    "url": "https://www.gov.uk/service-manual/user-research/how-user-research-improves-service-design",
                    "text": "Read more about user research"
                },
                "image": "/assets/images/illustration-sketches/user-research.webp",
                "imageAlt": "A diagram showing a user research process with connected steps",
                "icon": "user",
                "colour": "text-violet-600 dark:text-violet-400"
            },
            {
                "title": "Accessibility",
                "description": "This means making sure that the service works for people with disabilities, and that it meets the requirements of the law. It includes things like making sure that the service works with screen readers, or that it can be used by people with colour blindness.",
                "link": {
                    "url": "https://accessibility.blog.gov.uk/2016/05/16/what-we-mean-when-we-talk-about-accessibility-2/",
                    "text": "Read more about accessibility"
                },
                "image": "/assets/images/illustration-sketches/accessibility.webp",
                "imageAlt": "A diagram showing a user with a screen reader and a keyboard",
                "colour": "text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400"
            },
            {
                "title": "Content design",
                "description": "This involves making sure that the words used in a service are clear and easy to understand. It also means making sure that the structure of the content is logical, and that users can find what they need.",
                "link": {
                    "url": "https://www.gov.uk/guidance/content-design/what-is-content-design",
                    "text": "Read more about content design"
                },
                "image": "/assets/images/illustration-sketches/content-design.webp",
                "imageAlt": "A diagram showing a user with a screen reader and a keyboard",
                "colour": "text-rose-600 dark:text-rose-400"
            }
        ] %}
    <div class="mt-4 md:mt-6 grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-4 md:gap-8">
        {% for service in services %}
            <div class="mb-5 flex h-full flex-col">
                {% if service.image %}
                    <div class="mb-3 flex h-36 w-full items-end rounded-lg dark:items-center dark:justify-center dark:border dark:border-zinc-300/30 dark:bg-white/95 dark:p-3 md:h-40">
                        <img src="{{ service.image }}"
                             alt="{{ service.imageAlt }}"
                             class="h-full w-auto rounded-lg object-contain"
                             loading="lazy"
                             decoding="async">
                    </div>
                {% endif %}
                <h2 class="heading-xs flex items-center gap-3">
                    {% if not service.image %}
                        <div 
                            class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-gray-100 dark:bg-zinc-800 border border-gray-200 dark:border-zinc-700 {{ service.colour }} shadow-sm h-10 w-10" 
                            aria-hidden="true"
                        >
                            <i data-lucide="{{ service.icon }}"
                               class="h-5 w-5"
                               aria-hidden="true"></i>
                        </div>
                    {% endif %}
                    {{ service.title }}
                </h2>
                <p class="body-m">{{ service.description }}</p>
                <p class="body-s mt-2">
                    <a href="{{ service.link.url }}"
                       class="text-link inline-flex items-center gap-1"
                       target="_blank"
                       rel="noopener noreferrer">
                        {{ service.link.text }}
                        <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                             aria-label="Opens in new tab"
                             class="w-4 h-4"
                             fill="none"
                             viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                             stroke="currentColor">
                            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M10 6H6a2 2 0 00-2 2v10a2 2 0 002 2h10a2 2 0 002-2v-4M14 4h6m0 0v6m0-6L10 14" />
                        </svg>
                        <span class="sr-only">(opens in a new tab)</span>
                    </a>
                </p>
            </div>
        {% endfor %}
    </div>
</section>
<section id="things-ive-done" class="py-8 md:py-10 lg:py-12 xl:py-14">
    <div>
        <h2 class="heading-m">Things I've done</h2>
        <div class="lg:w-2/3">
            <p class="body-m">
                I've provided design services on a wide range of projects, from small websites to large-scale digital transformation programmes. Projects have ranged from greenfield projects to others that have involved replacing legacy systems with new services. Ideally, I'm involved from the very start, but I'm used to being parachuted in to help with a specific problem.
            </p>
            <p class="body-m">
                Typically, the projects I work on are used by thousands of people every day, from members of the public completing a task online, to civil servants using a system to manage their work. There are too many to list here, but here are a few examples:
            </p>
        </div>
        {% set projectExamples = [
            {
                "client": "Education and Skills Funding Agency",
                "title": "Learner Data Service",
                "logo": "education-and-skills-funding-agency-logo.svg",
                "statement": "Designed a new service to make it simpler for further education providers to provide learner data to the Education and Skills Funding Agency (ESFA)",
                "detail": "Reduced friction in complex data submission journeys so providers could complete tasks with less manual effort."
            },
            {
                "client": "Home Office",
                "title": "Police National Computer",
                "logo": "home-office-logo.svg",
                "link": {
                    "url": "projects/home-office",
                    "text": "Redesigned the Police National Computer (PNC)"
                },
                "suffix": "to make it easier for police officers to manage stolen property records",
                "detail": "Focused on high-pressure operational workflows, helping officers find and update records more confidently."
            },
            {
                "client": "HM Prison & Probation Service",
                "title": "Prison Activities Management",
                "logo": "hmpps-logo.svg",
                "link": {
                    "url": "projects/hmpps",
                    "text": "Designed a service to replace the National Offender Management Service (NOMIS)"
                },
                "suffix": ", allowing prison staff to manage prisoner activities",
                "detail": "Improved day-to-day task clarity for prison teams working across complex activity and schedule management."
            },
            {
                "client": "Apprenticeships",
                "title": "Apprenticeship Service",
                "logo": "apprenticeships-logo.svg",
                "statement": "Provided design support to the Apprenticeship Service, helping to improve the service for employers and training providers",
                "detail": "Worked across design, content and delivery teams to improve usability and consistency across core journeys."
            },
            {
                "client": "Department for Education",
                "title": "Children's Social Care",
                "logo": "department-for-education-logo.svg",
                "link": {
                    "url": "projects/childrens-social-care",
                    "text": "Collaborated with the Children's Social Care team at the Department for Education"
                },
                "suffix": "to explore how digital tools could make social workers' day-to-day work easier",
                "detail": "Translated frontline insights into practical service concepts that could support social workers in real settings."
            },
            {
                "client": "Apprenticeships",
                "title": "Account Management Dashboard",
                "logo": "apprenticeships-logo.svg",
                "statement": "Redesigned the main account home page for the Apprenticeship Service, making it easier for employers to manage their accounts and start taking on apprentices",
                "detail": "Brought key actions together into a clearer dashboard so employers could manage accounts with less effort."
            }
        ] %}
        <div class="mb-4 mt-8">
            <div class="relative">
                <div id="things-done-viewport"
                     class="overflow-hidden"
                     role="region"
                     aria-label="Project examples carousel">
                    <ul id="things-done-cards"
                        class="flex gap-4 md:gap-5 lg:gap-6"
                        aria-label="Example projects"
                        tabindex="0"
                        role="list">
                        {% for project in projectExamples %}
                            <li class="things-done-card w-full shrink-0 lg:w-[calc(50%-0.75rem)]" 
                                aria-labelledby="project-{{ loop.index }}-title">
                                <div class="mb-3 flex h-16 items-center md:h-18 lg:h-20 xl:h-24">
                                    <img src="/assets/images/clients/{{ project.logo | replace('.svg', '--dark.svg') if (project.logo.endsWith('.svg')) else project.logo }}"
                                         alt="{{ project.client }} logo"
                                         width="260"
                                         height="88"
                                         class="hidden h-auto max-h-12 w-auto max-w-[12rem] object-contain dark:block md:max-h-14 md:max-w-[15rem] lg:max-h-16 lg:max-w-[17rem] xl:max-h-18 xl:max-w-[19rem]" />
                                    <img src="/assets/images/clients/{{ project.logo }}"
                                         alt="{{ project.client }} logo"
                                         width="260"
                                         height="88"
                                         class="block h-auto max-h-12 w-auto max-w-[12rem] object-contain dark:hidden md:max-h-14 md:max-w-[15rem] lg:max-h-16 lg:max-w-[17rem] xl:max-h-18 xl:max-w-[19rem]" />
                                </div>
                                <h3 id="project-{{ loop.index }}-title" 
                                    class="heading-xs">
                                    {{ project.title }}
                                </h3>
                                <p class="body-m">
                                    {% if project.statement %}
                                        {{ project.statement }}
                                    {% else %}
                                        <a href="{{ project.link.url }}"
                                           class="text-link">{{ project.link.text }}</a> {{ project.suffix }}
                                    {% endif %}
                                </p>
                                <p class="body-m mt-3">{{ project.detail }}</p>
                            </li>
                        {% endfor %}
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="mt-3 flex flex-col items-start gap-3 sm:mt-4 sm:gap-4 lg:mt-5 lg:gap-5">
                <div id="things-done-controls"
                     class="hidden items-center gap-3 sm:gap-4"
                     role="group"
                     aria-label="Project carousel navigation">
                    <button id="things-done-prev"
                            type="button"
                            class="group inline-flex h-10 w-10 items-center justify-center rounded-full border border-gray-300 bg-white text-gray-600 shadow-sm transition-all duration-200 hover:border-gray-400 hover:bg-gray-50 hover:text-gray-900 hover:shadow-md focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-blue-600 focus-visible:ring-offset-2 disabled:cursor-not-allowed disabled:opacity-50 disabled:hover:border-gray-300 disabled:hover:bg-white disabled:hover:shadow-sm dark:border-gray-600 dark:bg-gray-800 dark:text-gray-300 dark:hover:border-gray-500 dark:hover:bg-gray-700 dark:hover:text-gray-100 dark:focus-visible:ring-blue-400 dark:focus-visible:ring-offset-gray-950 dark:disabled:hover:border-gray-600 dark:disabled:hover:bg-gray-800 sm:h-11 sm:w-11"
                            title="View previous project examples"
                            aria-label="Go to previous project examples"
                            aria-controls="things-done-cards"
                            aria-describedby="things-done-status"
                            data-carousel-direction="previous">
                        <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" 
                             class="h-5 w-5 transition-transform duration-200 group-hover:-translate-x-0.5" 
                             fill="none" 
                             viewBox="0 0 24 24" 
                             stroke="currentColor" 
                             stroke-width="2"
                             aria-hidden="true"
                             role="img"
                             aria-labelledby="prev-icon-title">
                            <title id="prev-icon-title">Previous arrow</title>
                            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M15 19l-7-7 7-7" />
                        </svg>
                        <span class="sr-only">Previous project examples</span>
                    </button>
                    <button id="things-done-next"
                            type="button"
                            class="group inline-flex h-10 w-10 items-center justify-center rounded-full border border-gray-300 bg-white text-gray-600 shadow-sm transition-all duration-200 hover:border-gray-400 hover:bg-gray-50 hover:text-gray-900 hover:shadow-md focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-blue-600 focus-visible:ring-offset-2 disabled:cursor-not-allowed disabled:opacity-50 disabled:hover:border-gray-300 disabled:hover:bg-white disabled:hover:shadow-sm dark:border-gray-600 dark:bg-gray-800 dark:text-gray-300 dark:hover:border-gray-500 dark:hover:bg-gray-700 dark:hover:text-gray-100 dark:focus-visible:ring-blue-400 dark:focus-visible:ring-offset-gray-950 dark:disabled:hover:border-gray-600 dark:disabled:hover:bg-gray-800 sm:h-11 sm:w-11"
                            title="View next project examples"
                            aria-label="Go to next project examples"
                            aria-controls="things-done-cards"
                            aria-describedby="things-done-status"
                            data-carousel-direction="next">
                        <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" 
                             class="h-5 w-5 transition-transform duration-200 group-hover:translate-x-0.5" 
                             fill="none" 
                             viewBox="0 0 24 24" 
                             stroke="currentColor" 
                             stroke-width="2"
                             aria-hidden="true"
                             role="img"
                             aria-labelledby="next-icon-title">
                            <title id="next-icon-title">Next arrow</title>
                            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M9 5l7 7-7 7" />
                        </svg>
                        <span class="sr-only">Next project examples</span>
                    </button>
                </div>
                <p id="things-done-status"
                   class="sr-only"
                   aria-live="polite"></p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <p class="body-m">
            You can read more about <a href="/projects"
               class="text-link">projects I've worked on</a> recently.
        </p>
    </div>
</section>
<section id="work-with-me" class="py-8 md:py-10 lg:py-12 xl:py-14">
    <div class="md:w-2/3">
        <h2 class="heading-m">Work with me</h2>
        <p class="body-m">
            I'm willing to work with clients in a number of ways, depending on their needs. This can include working:
        </p>
        <ul class="mb-4 list-disc list-outside pl-5 body-m">
            <li class="mb-2">as part of an existing team</li>
            <li class="mb-2">with a team of associates</li>
            <li class="mb-2">with a partner agency</li>
            <li class="mb-2">directly with the client</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="body-m">
            Although I prefer to work remotely, I can travel to meet clients if needed. I'm conveniently based in the centre of the UK, and can easily travel to London, Birmingham, Manchester, and other major cities.
        </p>
        <p class="body-m">
            I'm used to working with clients' existing tools and processes, particularly in the Public Sector where security is a priority.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-8 callout-rail callout-rail-default">
        <h3 class="heading-s">Let's discuss your project</h3>
        <p class="body-m w-full md:w-3/4 lg:w-2/3">I'll help you understand your users' needs and design services that deliver <span class="font-medium">measurable improvements</span> and <span class="font-medium">return on investment</span>.</p>
        <p class="body-m">
            <a href="/contact" class="text-link">
                Get in touch
            </a>
        </p>
    </div>
</section>
<section id="continue-your-journey" class="pb-8 md:pb-10 lg:pb-12 xl:pb-14">
    <div class="md:w-2/3">
        <p class="body-m">
            If you'd like to keep exploring, you can browse <a href="/projects" class="text-link">project case studies</a>, read my <a href="/writing" class="text-link">writing</a>, see <a href="/service-design" class="text-link">how I approach service design</a>, learn more <a href="/about" class="text-link">about me</a>, or <a href="/contact" class="text-link">get in touch</a> about your project.
        </p>
    </div>
</section>
